   692‚Üí### Parse
   694‚ÜíThe engine which parses the contents of your file containing environment
   695‚Üívariables is available to use. It accepts a String or Buffer and will return
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   705‚Üí#### Options
   707‚Üí##### debug
   709‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   710‚Üí
   711‚ÜíTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   712‚Üí
   713‚Üí```js
   714‚Üíconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   715‚Üíconst buf = Buffer.from('hello world')
   716‚Üíconst opt = { debug: true }
   717‚Üíconst config = dotenv.parse(buf, opt)
   718‚Üí// expect a debug message because the buffer is not in KEY=VAL form
   719‚Üí```
   720‚Üí
   721‚Üí### Populate
   723‚ÜíThe engine which populates the contents of your .env file to `process.env` is available for use. It accepts a target, a source, and options. This is useful for power users who want to supply their own objects.
   724‚Üí
